		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200855</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Quantum Motion has announced a successfully closed $160 million Series C funding round. The funding is intended to be used for the commercialisation of the company&#8217;s unique silicon-based quantum computing</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quantum Motion Raises $160 Million for Quantum Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://quantummotion.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Motion</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has announced a successfully closed $160 million Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/illoca-raises-13m-to-reinvent-architectural-design/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The funding is intended to be used for the commercialisation of the company&#8217;s unique silicon-based quantum computing technologya feat many believe will be a turning point for the industry.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round was led by DCVC and Kembara, the high-tech fund from Mundi Ventures, with a sizable £40m anchor round from the British Business Bank. Other participants included Firgun, plus existing strategic investors such as Bosch Ventures, Porsche Automobil Holding SE and Oxford Science Enterprises.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this funding, Quantum Motion has racked up over $210 million in total. This makes it the best funded quantum hardware startup in the UK.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Silicon Advantage: Scaling Within the Rack</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Motion is betting on silicon CMOS technology, whereas many quantum competitors rely on exotic materials or large, custom &#8220;fridge&#8221; architectures that use multi-megawatt levels of power. The chips in every contemporary laptop and smartphone are made using the same basic manufacturing technique.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200856" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200856" class="size-full wp-image-200856" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Quantum-Motion.jpg" alt="Quantum Motion" width="480" height="119" /><p id="caption-attachment-200856" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Quantum Motion</p></div>
<p>Quantum Motion uses standard silicon transistors to create qubits, avoiding the huge infrastructure problems faced by others. The company says its methods create utility-scale quantum systems 100 times smaller, cheaper, and using 1,000 times less energy. &#8220;Quantum computing will only achieve its full potential if built on a platform that scales,&#8221; said Dr. James Palles-Dimmock.</p>
<p>&#8220;We believe silicon is the strongest route to achieving that. Our goal is to deliver commercially viable quantum computers that don&#8217;t require their own power plants or specialised aircraft hangars but instead fit right into standard 19-inch data centre racks.&#8221;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/illoca-raises-13m-to-reinvent-architectural-design/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Illoca Raises $13M to Reinvent Architectural Design</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Proven Milestone at the NQCC</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new investment comes after a significant year for the startup. In late 2025, Quantummotion delivered and installed a complete stack quantum computer with conventional silicon chips at the NQCC (National Quantum Computing Centre) in Harwell, UK.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This deployment demonstrated that a fully integrated, portable solution that incorporated the quantum processor with control electronics and software in a single server rack footprint could meet all of the performance requirements of a practical test bed.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Additionally, the firm has progressed to Stage B of the US Defence Advanced Research Projects Agency’s (DARPA) Quantum Benchmarking Initiative. This is a detailed test as to which quantum methodologies will make it to &#8220;utility scale&#8221;, the stage where a quantum computer can achieve a task that even the world’s fastest supercomputers will not be able to handle.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Global Expansion and Strategic Goals</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $160 million in fresh capital, Quantum Motion is moving from the lab to the factory. The funds will be used to:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Accelerate Commercialisation:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Speed up the delivery of utility-scale systems to early-access partners in finance, materials science, and pharmaceuticals.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Deepen Manufacturing Ties:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expand its partnership with GlobalFoundries, one of the world’s largest semiconductor foundries, to ensure mass producibility of its qubit chips.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Global Footprint:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Bolster its newly opened international offices and laboratories in Spain and Australia, tapping into global talent pools in quantum engineering.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As AI workloads continue to strain the world’s power grids, the demand for more energy-efficient, high-performance computing has never been higher. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By aligning quantum growth with the existing silicon supply chain, Quantum Motion is positioning itself not just as a hardware provider but as the architect of the next generation of the sustainable data centre.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quantum Motion Raises $160 Million for Quantum Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
