					<description><![CDATA[<p>AI-native design startup Illoca announced today it has raised $13 million in seed funding. The round was led by Bessemer Venture Partners and also received investments from AIX Ventures, Root</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/illoca-raises-13m-to-reinvent-architectural-design/" data-wpel-link="internal">Illoca Raises $13M to Reinvent Architectural Design</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI-native design startup </span><a href="https://illoca.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Illoca </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">announced today it has raised $13 million in seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The round was led by Bessemer Venture Partners and also received investments from AIX Ventures, Root Ventures and Alt Ventures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This investment couldn&#8217;t have come at a better time for the profession. Architects have been plagued with decade-old, legacy CAD software, and the design industry as a whole has been in the midst of a revolution in hardware and software innovation. Yet architects have been kept busy with what feels like a good 70% of their time spent &#8220;transcribing&#8221; ideas from sketches into rigid, 3D, millimetre-accurate Revit models. Illoca strives to get that time back.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridging the &#8220;Creation Gap&#8221;</span></h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Founded in 2024 by Chin-Yi Cheng and Chiaowei Yu, Illoca is built on deep technical and industry expertise. Cheng previously pioneered generative AI at Google DeepMind and the Autodesk AI Lab. Yu served as BIM lead at Tesla, managing the design of the world&#8217;s most complex manufacturing facilities.</p>
<div id="attachment_200822" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200822" class="wp-image-200822 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Illoca.jpg" alt="Illoca" width="400" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-200822" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Illoca</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Their flagship product, Tracing Paper&#x2122;, is described as the industry’s first truly generative interface for schematic design. Unlike previous tools that merely automated small tasks, Tracing Paper allows architects to:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Sketch to 3D</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Import a hand-sketched diagram or bubble diagram and produce an immediately editable 2- or 3-dimensional model.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Natural Language Interaction</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Use conversation prompts, such as &#8220;move the components onto the right&#8221;, to modify the layout or structure.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Smooth delivery</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Export &#8216;construction-ready&#8217; data directly into software used by professionals today so that our AI-generated concepts are not just pretty pictures but constructible buildings.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Nyobolt Raises $60M, Hits $1B Valuation</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Precision Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Historically, however, the biggest challenge of using generative AI for architecture has been precision. </span>Tools like Midjourney produce beautiful visuals but lack the &#8220;groundedness&#8221; needed for code, compliance, and structural applications.</p>
<p>&#8220;Any architect can generate code-compliant designs in just the time it takes to open a file,&#8221; said Bessemer Venture Partners. By combining LLMs with geometric kernels, Illoca ensures &#8220;creative flow&#8221; is never interrupted by technical software limitations.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Looking Ahead: A More Efficient Built World</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The original $13 million will fund the expansion of Illoca’s engineering team and enable it to speed up the development of its AI engine. With global demand for housing, healthcare and resilient infrastructure at record levels, the productivity improvements proposed by Illoca could be a game changer for the architecture, engineering and construction (AEC) industry.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this new capital, Illoca is not just building a faster tool; it is attempting to re-architect the very relationship between human creativity and the digital environment.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/illoca-raises-13m-to-reinvent-architectural-design/" data-wpel-link="internal">Illoca Raises $13M to Reinvent Architectural Design</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
