					<description><![CDATA[<p>OpenTrade, a top institutional-grade platform for on-chain lending and yield products, said it had closed $17 million of strategic funding in a recent round. This fundraising comes as the world&#8217;s</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/opentrade-raises-17m-for-stablecoin-yield-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">OpenTrade Raises $17M for Stablecoin Yield Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.opentrade.io/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenTrade</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a top institutional-grade platform for on-chain lending and yield products, said it had closed $17 million of strategic </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">in a recent round. This fundraising comes as the world&#8217;s stablecoin market cap passes the $300 billion mark, representing a huge transformation in the way in which fintechs and legacy financial institutions handle liquidity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenTrade completed a $7.8M round, led by Mercury Fund and Notion Capital, and also included heavy investments from a16z Crypto, AlbionVC and CMCC Global. The fundraising now stands at more than $30M after several record-breaking growth achievements in 2024 and 2025.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling the &#8220;Bridge&#8221; to Real-World Assets</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenTrade was created by Dave Sutter and Jeff Handler (both ex-Centre USDC governance consortium) to create a solution that brings together the efficiency of stablecoins and the stability of RWAs. The platform enables fintechs, neobanks and exchanges to deliver dollar- and euro-denominated yield products to their users, backed by first-class assets including US T-bills and commercial paper.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200804" style="width: 408px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200804" class="size-full wp-image-200804" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/OpenTrade.png" alt="OpenTrade" width="398" height="398" /><p id="caption-attachment-200804" class="wp-caption-text">Source: OpenTrade</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;The demand for yield infrastructure is growing exponentially,&#8221; said Dave Sutter, CEO of OpenTrade. &#8220;We’ve built the &#8216;plumbing&#8217; that allows any financial institution to integrate institutional-grade stablecoin yield without having to build their own investment or custody stacks from scratch.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new capital is earmarked for three primary growth areas:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Infrastructure Expansion</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Developing both permissioned (compliant/regulated) and permissionless (DeFi-native) pathways for yield.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Curation+ Framework</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Scaling its &#8220;Curation+&#8221; service, which allows partners to design custom, active yield strategies managed by regulated asset managers.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Team Growth</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Increasing headcount across engineering, asset management, and customer success to support a global client base.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nyobolt-raises-60m-hits-1b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Nyobolt Raises $60M, Hits $1B Valuation</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Institutional Momentum</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">OpenTrade’s growth metrics underscore the rising appetite for its services. The company recently surpassed $200 million in Total Value Locked (TVL) and processed more than $250 million in transaction volume in 2025 alone. With the first four months of 2026 already seeing $300 million in activity, the firm projects it will exceed $1 billion in transaction volume by year-end.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform has already secured major partnerships with fintech leaders such as Littio in Colombia and Midas Kripto in Turkey, helping these firms provide &#8220;digital dollar&#8221; savings products to users in inflation-prone markets.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Navigating the Regulatory Landscape</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fundraiser comes at a critical juncture for the industry as U.S. lawmakers debate the CLARITY Act, a digital asset bill that could reshape how stablecoin rewards are distributed. While the act may prohibit interest on idle balances, it is expected to permit usage-based rewards. A framework for OpenTrade’s legal architecture is already designed to navigate.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Our structure is derived from traditional securities lending,&#8221; Sutter noted. &#8220;By remaining compliant with both traditional finance and digital asset standards, we’re providing the safety and scale that CFOs and institutional treasurers require.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/opentrade-raises-17m-for-stablecoin-yield-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">OpenTrade Raises $17M for Stablecoin Yield Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
